title: Cabrillo National Monument: People
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     History & Culture     People               People         San Salvador Build Site     San Salvador Build Site (closed as of July 30, 2015) The San Diego Maritime Museum, in partnership with Cabrillo National Monument, has built an historically-accurate, fully-sailable replica of the San Salvador, Cabrillo's flagship. It was placed in the water on July 30, 2015. For more information, please visit www.sdmaritime.org.  Â    Juan Rodriguez Cabrillo - Learn more about the history of Cabrillo. Kumeyaay - Learn how the Kumeyaay are part of the history of Cabrillo. Conquistador Clothing - Here you can learn about some of the period clothing during Cabrillo's time. Living History - In this section you can learn about the Living History Program
